Job Title: Manager Investment Analytics and Insights Operations
Ad Text:
Company description:



About Us

The Department of Transport and Planning oversees key planning, transport and land use policy decisions and management across the State. A life-cycle approach to planning, building, connecting and sustaining communities means our people can come together to; improve services, deliver sustainable projects, focus on customer engagement, streamline regulatory approval pathways, facilitate community consultation and better realise local economic opportunities for more liveable communities across Victoria.

Network Design and Integration delivers transport priorities through the planning, development and maintenance of an integrated pipeline of projects and strategic initiatives that provide safe, efficient and sustainable outcomes to all Victorians. We're focused on outcomes that deliver more choice, connections and confidence in our travel, ensuring the whole transport network works as one to deliver better services and outcomes.



Job description:



About the Role

The Manager, Investment Modelling, Analytics & Insights Operations leads a team delivering investment modelling and analytics across DTP and franchisees for both road and rail assets. The role oversees daily operations, develops and maintains long-term lifecycle models, undertakes modelling to inform asset renewal and maintenance plans, and contributes to multidisciplinary projects. It also manages rail and road modelling artefacts, reviews asset condition data, produces insights for stakeholders, and drives continuous improvement while fostering effective relationships in a complex, dynamic environment.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position Outcomes / Accountabilities

Leadership - Manager operations is accountable for establishing an ongoing annual modelling task plan, leading and supervising the operations team and its assigned functions to ensure delivery of high-quality work in alignment with current strategies and in line with the annual task plan.
Effective Lifecycle Planning and Cost Analysis - As the functional lead of the Investment Analytics and Insights Operations team, manager will develop and sustain investment analytics capabilities across rail and road networks to enable DTP to be informed custodian of the rail and road infrastructure.
Continuous Improvement Strategy and Culture - Manager successfully foster a culture of engagement, participation and shared understanding across different stakeholders in relation to continuous improvement practices that aligned with the priorities of the Asset Intelligence department.
Stakeholder Liaison and Management - The Manager builds a strong and effective working relationship with stakeholders; facilitates innovative solutions to resolve stakeholder competing needs. Acts as the key point of contact and

Key Selection Criteria

The DTP is seeking a dynamic leader with strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills, capable of delivering effective solutions while considering broader business impacts. The role requires exceptional stakeholder management, high-impact communication, and commercial acumen to drive value and manage organisational risk. Applicants should demonstrate expertise in data and digital literacy, foster innovation and continuous improvement, effectively manage teams, and show flexibility to adapt strategies to achieve optimal outcomes.

Qualifications and Experience

Mandatory

Tertiary qualification in engineering, asset management or an equivalent qualification.
Extensive demonstrated experience in asset management, Insights Analytics and life cycle planning
Demonstratable experience in leading a team

Desirable

Demonstrated experience in change management
Demonstrated experience in systems engineering

Culture Value

We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

What we offer

Meaningful work making Victorian communities more accessible and liveable
Professional growth and development opportunities across the department and the wider Victorian Public Services
A hybrid working model focused on collaboration and teamwork
Optimal work-life balance initiatives including flexible working arrangements
Opportunity to work across multiple urban and suburban hubs
We prioritise the development of a safe and inclusive culture

Pre-employment checks and employment conditions

All new appointments to the department will be subject to a National Criminal Records Check, Misconduct Screening, and a Qualification Check where there is a requirement for a mandatory qualification. Information provided to the Department of Transport and Planning will be treated in the strictest confidence consistent with the requirements of the Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.

Recipients of Victorian Public Service (VPS) voluntary departure packages should note that re-employment restrictions apply.

Non-VPS applicants will be subject to a probation period of six months.

How to Apply

Click the ‘Apply' button to be redirected to our recruitment platform, where you may need to create an account to submit your application. If you encounter any issues, refer to our Quick Reference Guide for step-by-step instructions.

Applications close at 11:59 pm on Wednesday 10 December 2025.

Please include both your resume and a cover letter. All applications must be submitted via the online portal, we're unable to accept email or manual submissions.

For further information about the role, please contact Raman Pelia, Senior Manager Investment Modelling, Analytics & Insights via 0449 944 391 or Raman.Pelia@transport.vic.gov.au

Important Information:

If you require any adjustments to fully participate in the recruitment process, or need the advert or attachments in an accessible format (e.g., large print), please contact us by phone or email. We're here to support you.

Job Title: Manager Investment Analytics and Insights Assurance
Ad Text:
Company description:



About Us

The Department of Transport and Planning oversees key planning, transport and land use policy decisions and management across the State. A life-cycle approach to planning, building, connecting and sustaining communities means our people can come together to; improve services, deliver sustainable projects, focus on customer engagement, streamline regulatory approval pathways, facilitate community consultation and better realise local economic opportunities for more liveable communities across Victoria.

Network Design and Integration delivers transport priorities through the planning, development and maintenance of an integrated pipeline of projects and strategic initiatives that provide safe, efficient and sustainable outcomes to all Victorians. We're focused on outcomes that deliver more choice, connections and confidence in our travel, ensuring the whole transport network works as one to deliver better services and outcomes.



Job description:



About the Role

The Manager, Investment Modelling, Analytics & Insights Assurance leads a team that reviews and assures investment modelling activities across DTP and its franchisees for both rail and road assets. The role oversees the evaluation of modelling artefacts, data quality, franchisee reports, and asset condition data, and produces regular assurance reports. It also develops and maintains modelling processes, supports multidisciplinary asset projects, coordinates assurance compliance, and drives continuous improvement and roadmap development for analytics and insights models.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position Outcomes / Accountabilities

Effective Lifecycle Planning and Cost Analysis - As the functional lead of the Investment Analytics and Insights Assurance team, manager is accountable for developing and sustaining investment analytics and assurance capabilities across rail and road networks to enable DTP to be informed custodian of the rail and road infrastructure.
Assurance and Reporting - Manager assurance is accountable for reviewing the rail operator and road infrastructure asset investment models, conducting periodic evaluations in line with contractual requirements. as well as internal department operating requirements. Where appropriate, findings were used to inform and enhance the department's own models.
Leadership - Liaise with Transport Services regarding the expected delivery, assurance and close out of artefact and data provided by Franchisee. Manager will be leading the embedment and provide oversight of assurance practices across the wider investment Modelling, Analytics & Insights Team.
Stakeholder Liaison and Management - The Manager builds a strong and effective working relationship with stakeholders (including other business areas, MR5 contract assurance team, heavy rail and light rail operators.
Continuous Improvement Strategy and Culture - Manager successfully foster a culture of engagement, participation and shared understanding across different stakeholders in relation to continuous improvement assurance practices that aligned with the priorities of the Asset Intelligence department.

Key Selection Criteria

The DTP is seeking a leader with strong stakeholder management and impactful communication skills to guide complex engagements and provide high-level advice to diverse audiences. The role requires a forward-thinking professional who drives innovation, continuous improvement and evidence-based problem solving, while demonstrating strong commercial acumen and effective team management. Applicants should bring accomplished data literacy, including developing data models and translating insights into decisions, along with applied digital and technological capability to support modern tools and processes.

Qualifications and Experience

Mandatory

Tertiary qualification in engineering, asset management or an equivalent qualification.
Extensive demonstrated experience in asset management, Insights Analytics and life cycle planning
Demonstratable experience in leading a team

Desirable

Demonstrated experience in change management.
Demonstrated experience in systems engineering

Culture Value

We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

What we offer

Meaningful work making Victorian communities more accessible and liveable
Professional growth and development opportunities across the department and the wider Victorian Public Services
A hybrid working model focused on collaboration and teamwork
Optimal work-life balance initiatives including flexible working arrangements
Opportunity to work across multiple urban and suburban hubs
We prioritise the development of a safe and inclusive culture

Pre-employment checks and employment conditions

All new appointments to the department will be subject to a National Criminal Records Check, Misconduct Screening, and a Qualification Check where there is a requirement for a mandatory qualification. Information provided to the Department of Transport and Planning will be treated in the strictest confidence consistent with the requirements of the Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.

About the Agency
 
This Federal Government agency plays a vital role in shaping aged care policy and funding frameworks across Australia. Through data-driven insights and innovative solutions, they ensure transparency, sustainability, and quality care for older Australians.
 
About the Role

EL1 Senior Data Analyst - Aged Care 
12-month labour hire contract (with strong potential to extend through 2027/2028)
Classification: EL1
In this role, you'll lead analytical initiatives that strengthen aged care accommodation policy and compliance. Working closely with the Director and internal teams, you'll design data solutions, improve reporting processes, and provide expert advice to inform strategic decisions.
 
Key Responsibilities

Design and implement data solutions using MS Excel to meet operational needs.
Analyse and interpret data holdings from MS Access databases to answer policy questions.
Create continuity tools - develop policies and procedures for replicating queries and formulas post-contract.
Enhance analytical frameworks for improved price comparison and reporting.
Produce technical papers and reports for advisory committees and executive briefings.
Provide expert advice across the Aged Care Accommodation section and broader policy branch.
About You
 
To be eligible, you must be an Australian Citizen and demonstrate:

Strong technical and analytical skills in mathematics, data analysis, and interpretation.
Experience with SAS, SQL, MS Excel, or Python (MS Access optional).
Ability to communicate complex technical issues clearly to non-technical audiences.
Excellent organisational skills and ability to manage competing priorities.
Qualifications in mathematics, statistics, or related fields (highly regarded).
 
Why Join?

Influence aged care systems that impact Australians nationwide.
Work in a collaborative, purpose-driven environment.
Enjoy flexible arrangements and opportunities for professional growth.
 
How to Apply? Apply directly through Seek.com.  For more information about this role, contact Donna Knight, dknight@onqrecruitment.com.au

Join a team that's All Kinds of Useful

At Origin, being useful is more than a tagline - it's how we approach work every day. As a collective, we're a team that thrives on finding better ways, working together, and owning our impact. From powering homes to delivering award-winning internet and helping to lead Australia's energy transition. If you're driven by purpose and excited to be part of something bigger, we'd love to have you on the journey.

The Role

The Analyst is part of the Billing and Metering operations team and reports to the Market Data- Team Leader. The Market Data Analyst is responsible for proactively managing performance of third-party suppliers, managing and reviewing data exceptions and understanding metering regulations, contractual and industry requirements. This is for Electricity, Gas & Hot Water.


Responsibilities:

Build and manage strong relationships with third party suppliers to improve service levels and drive performance associated with meter data, standing data and services
Build and maintain strong relationships with internal stakeholders
Monitor and validate incoming meter data to ensure volumes and quality conform with market requirements
Utilise reporting to identify performance trends from third parties and develop strategies for improvement
Undertake special data analysis assignments to support Meter Data as well as other stakeholders
Provide support with Business Improvement initiatives
Identify and take action to correct errors
Respond to enquiries from downstream and other users relating to meter and standing data
Carry out root cause analysis of exceptions and implement required solutions to minimise or eliminate exceptions numbers
CAD related actions to ensure our CAD obligations are met



About You
To be considered for the role you will have:

At least 2 years' experience in the Energy Industry
Experience dealing with third parties, in particular service performance.
At least 2 years' experience in data analytics
Ability to understand and apply Energy Market systems rules and regulations, including, Metrology, Meter Data, B2B transactions and MSATS.

Origin - Where good change happens

At Origin, we're powered by people who believe in creating change.


We are committed to fostering a diverse, gender equitable workforce, where everyone is welcome, and all applications are evaluated on merit and potential. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, people living with disabilities, culturally diverse people, any stage in life, people with intersex variations and people within LGBTQ+ communities, including trans and gender diverse.


Enjoy a challenging career in an exciting industry where you can grow and explore your potential. If you think you have transferable skills, an appetite to learn and would be a great fit, we'd love to hear from you.


Here's a little about us: https://www.originenergy.com.au/about/careers/

Background checks may be required to determine your suitability for this position as part of the recruitment process and during your employment. These checks may include police checks, AusCheck, medical assessment and/or drug and alcohol testing.

Please note unsolicited CVs from agencies will not be accepted.

About the Role
Join a high-impact Federal Government digital program as a Senior Lead Business Analyst. You will play a key role in driving major digital initiatives, leading discovery, analysis, and solution design within a multi-disciplinary team. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to nationally significant digital transformation work starting January 2026.

About the Opportunity
As the Lead Business Analyst, you'll collaborate with product, delivery, architecture, business and technical teams to shape solutions, drive clarity in requirements, support testing, and ensure successful delivery across a dynamic program of work.

Key Responsibilities

Lead analysis activities across multiple digital products.

Facilitate workshops with internal/external stakeholders to explore pain points, opportunities, and solution directions.

Produce essential project artefacts: user stories, process maps, blueprints, journey maps, personas, functional specs.

Drive requirement clarity, manage changes, and ensure alignment with program objectives.

Support solution design aligned to enterprise architecture, data, information management, and security needs.

Work closely in a multi-disciplinary team including Solution Architect, Product Manager, Delivery Manager, BA, developers, and testers.

What We're Looking For
Essential:
✔ 5+ years senior-level business analysis experience
✔ Strong stakeholder management, negotiation & problem-solving skills
✔ Exceptional communication skills (written & verbal)
✔ Experience producing BA artefacts, process maps, requirements, user stories, acceptance criteria, business cases

Desirable:
✓ Experience with Microsoft Dynamics 365 CRM
✓ Experience using Miro, Azure DevOps, or similar tools

Additional Requirements:

Must hold, or be able to obtain, Baseline security clearance

Hybrid work (ACT/NSW)

Senior/EL1 equivalent

6-month contract + 6-month extensions (up to 12 additional months)

Start date: 5 January 2026

If you are a Senior BA ready to step into a lead role in a major government program, we'd love to hear from you. Apply today.

About the role

In this role you will:

Support and administer the SQL-based energy and emissions reporting database

Develop and implement program and configuration changes to reflect evolving regulations and equipment

Build robust data quality checks to support annual audits and compliance

Document database work processes and maintain clear technical records

Improve reporting processes and dashboards (incl. Power BI) to support field operations, corporate reporting and leadership decision-making

Contribute to team goal setting, planning and budgeting, and play an active role in a strong team culture of care




Key stakeholders

You’ll work closely with:

Engineering and other technical teams

Safety, Health & Environment colleagues

Operations and Maintenance personnel and contractors

Regulators, auditors and other external stakeholders




About you

You will bring:

A Bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline

4+ years’ experience with accounting or data management systems

Strong data analytics skills, including validation, auditing and interpretation

Familiarity with National Greenhouse and Energy Reporting Scheme (NGERS) requirements

Exposure to oil and gas operations (highly regarded, not essential) and the ability to understand engineering concepts behind the data

Proven ability to coordinate with IT and technical teams to resolve system issues and implement changes

Strong organisational skills, able to deliver to deadlines and adapt to changing priorities

Proficiency in Microsoft Office and Power BI

Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to produce clear technical and business documentation

12 month-contract

$545/day plus super

Location Parramatta, hybrid

As a Senior Workforce Advisor, you will be responsible for undertaking and managing data requests, providing timely and accurate information to internal stakeholders, and delivering high-quality analysis and reporting. This is a key role that combines technical expertise with a strong customer-service focus to support workforce planning and broader organisational goals.

Key responsibilities

Manage and respond to workforce data requests, ensuring accurate, timely, and relevant information is delivered to stakeholders.

Provide expert advice on workforce data, systems, and analytical methods to support internal decision-making.

Utilise a range of systems and tools (e.g. SAP, iSeries, TRIM, Power BI, Alteryx, Excel, SQL, R, Python) to analyse and visualise data effectively.

Apply advanced analytical and problem-solving skills to produce evidence-based insights that inform strategic planning and improve student outcomes.

Prepare high-quality reports and recommendations, and work with your supervisor to develop an annual work plan outlining key responsibilities and success measures.

You

Demonstrated experience in workforce analytics, data reporting, or a related role.

Proficiency in data tools and technologies such as Power BI, Alteryx, SQL, Python, or R.

Strong communication skills, with the ability to convey complex information in a clear and compelling manner.

A proactive and organised approach, with strong attention to detail and a commitment to continuous improvement.

Experience working with HR systems such as SAP and TRIM is highly desirable.

Apply Now!

About Mason Stevens

Mason Stevens is a leading provider of integrated wealth platform technology, that uniquely focuses on investor portfolio outcomes. More than just an administration platform, the innovative technology, paired with experienced investment specialist support, empowers advisers to deliver on their clients’ investment objectives via an unconstrained investment universe, and backed by exceptional client service.

Established in 2010, Mason Stevens is privately owned with over $10 billion of funds under administration and management. Led by some of Australia’s most experienced finance, technology, and investment professionals, with over 80 staff nationally.

About the Role

The Business Analyst plays a key role in identifying operational challenges and designing effective solutions that support business goals. Working across multiple departments, this role helps implement and maintain business information systems that enhance performance and efficiency.

You’ll collaborate closely with financial reporting and IT teams to develop strategies that optimise costs and improve reporting outcomes. This role requires strong analytical thinking, cross-functional engagement, and a focus on delivering practical, data-driven improvements across platforms and operations.

Key Responsibilities:

Identify, create, and facilitate requirements elicitation by conducting business and systems process analysis and design.

Identifying business needs by focusing on quality improvement and data management.

Partner with a range of stakeholders to ensure requirements are aligned to meet the long-term business strategies.

Manage and coordinate various platform and business operations projects to monitor and report on the project outcomes to ensure they are delivered on time, within budget and to agreed quality standards.

Work with stakeholders, subject matter experts and project teams to develop, plan and implement testing, change management and training plans.

Assist concurrently on multiple projects while working closely with the Chief Technology Officer on platform strategy.

Required Skills/Experience/Knowledge:

Demonstrated experience in a Business Analyst role (minimum 3 years’ experience). 

Experience in working with a diverse range of stakeholders and applying change management principles through large and complex digital transformation projects. 

Ability to work autonomously to further scope future projects. 

Demonstrated experience in a range of methods, tools and techniques to capture requirements and evaluate and recommend appropriate solutions.

An appropriate tertiary qualification in a relevant discipline is desirable.

Excellent analytical, organisational, and communication skills.

Qualifications:

Tertiary degree, finance related discipline (preferred).

Ideally, 2 – 4 years’ experience in a client facing role within financial services.

Life at Mason Stevens

At Mason Stevens, relationships matter to us, and by fostering a culture of humility and collaboration, we achieve remarkable outcomes while supporting each individual to realise their potential.

We are committed to building and maintaining a diverse and talented team, backed by the belief that it is only by working together, that we will achieve our purpose; helping our Clients to realise better tomorrows.

We believe in keeping our ‘minds wide open’ and empowering people with the resources and trust needed to make a meaningful difference. We know an idea can only change lives if it happens, and value the kind of people who believe in being the change they seek and see opportunity in challenge.

Above all, we know you will be a great fit for us if you value people, show kindness and play fair.

Kindly note that Australian full work rights are required for this application.

Job Title: Senior Business Process Consultant - SAP Business Data Cloud & Analytics...
Ad Text:
We help the world run betterAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we'll bring out the best in you. We're builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what's next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You'll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What's in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed. 

Role Overview

Are you passionate about the transformative power of cloud data and analytics? Are you ready to help Australia’s public and private sectors unlock greater efficiency and insight through smarter data strategies and migrations?

Join SAP and play a leading role in redefining how organisations harness the potential of SAP Business Data Cloud and advanced analytics. As a Senior Business Process Consultant, you will architect and design complex data and analytics solutions, provide strategic leadership, and guide teams to deliver impactful outcomes. This is your opportunity to set new industry benchmarks and drive real transformation where it matters most.

Key Responsibilities

Architect and design end-to-end data management and analytics solutions using SAP Business Data Cloud, ensuring scalability, security, and alignment with industry best practices.

Provide strategic advisory to clients, developing data strategies and roadmaps that align with organisational objectives and compliance requirements.

Lead and mentor delivery teams, providing technical direction and best practice guidance at both regional and, where required, global levels.

Engage with senior stakeholders (including C-level executives) to understand business needs, facilitate workshops, and drive business use case discovery.

Oversee the implementation of data integration, modelling, and analytics solutions, ensuring quality and consistency across projects.

Maintain deep expertise in SAP’s data and analytics portfolio, with a focus on SAP Datasphere, SAP Analytics Cloud, and SAP HANA Cloud.

Foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning within project teams and across the wider SAP community.

Contribute to the development of best practices, technical documentation, and knowledge sharing across teams.

Support the sales process as a subject matter expert, including proposal development, solution scoping, and customer presentations.

Ensure adherence to SAP and client project methodologies, including Activate and relevant frameworks.

Education, Skills & Competencies

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Business Administration, Computer Science, Information Management, or a related field.

Proven expertise in solution architecture and design for large-scale data and analytics platforms, ideally within the SAP ecosystem.

Strong experience with SAP data and analytics solutions (such as SAP Analytics Cloud, SAP Datasphere, SAP HANA Cloud, or similar platforms), with the ability and motivation to rapidly learn and apply new SAP Business Data Cloud capabilities.

Demonstrated ability to lead, guide, and instruct teams across regions and, where required, globally, fostering knowledge transfer and capability uplift.

Solid understanding of cloud concepts, data architecture, and enterprise data management.

Demonstrated experience working with or for government agencies or large enterprises.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to present complex concepts to non-technical audiences.

Proven ability to capture business requirements and translate them into effective data solutions.

Beneficial

Experience with modern data platforms such as Databricks and/or Snowflake.

Hands-on experience in artificial intelligence (AI), particularly with SAP Business AI or similar enterprise AI solutions.

Experience in business planning and financial processes (e.g., SAP BPC, SAP Planning, or similar solutions).

Knowledge of ABAP programming and its application within SAP data and analytics environments.

Personal Attributes

High integrity, reliability, and ability to work effectively under pressure.

Self-starter with a passion for learning and staying ahead of technology trends.

Team player with strong interpersonal skills and a collaborative, inclusive mindset.

Customer-Facing Skills

Ability to inspire confidence and engage with stakeholders at all levels, including executives.

Skilled at delivering clear, concise presentations and facilitating workshops.

Travel

Willingness to travel as required, primarily within Brisbane and occasionally interstate or internationally.

What We Offer

At SAP, you’ll join a dynamic, inclusive, and flexible work environment, with opportunities for personal and professional growth, recognition for your unique contributions, and the chance to make a real impact on digital transformation in Australia.

Bring out your bestSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.  

Please note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.

Lead the Future of Data & Analytics Transformation – Join Our Centre of Excellence
Are you passionate about the transformative power of cloud data and analytics? Are you ready to help Australia’s public sector unlock greater efficiency and insight through smarter data strategies and migrations?
Join SAP and take the lead in a bold new initiative that’s redefining how key government agencies harness the potential of SAP Business Data Cloud and advanced analytics. With the establishment of a Centre of Excellence (CoE) for Federal Australian Agencies, we’re assembling a high-performance team to guide major agencies through the “how” of data and analytics transformation—delivering proven strategy, expert implementation, and scalable, lasting impact.
This high-profile, strategic initiative will begin as an 18-month transformation programme, serving as your initial assignment. Upon completion, you’ll transition into the broader Customer Success and Delivery area, extending best practices and knowledge gained to drive ongoing value for our clients. This is your opportunity to set new industry benchmarks and drive real transformation where it matters most.
As a Principal Business Process Consultant specialising in SAP Business Data Cloud and Analytics, you will architect and design complex data and analytics solutions, provide strategic leadership, and guide both regional and global teams. You will play a key role in shaping strategy, delivering impactful solutions, and building trusted relationships with government stakeholders.
Please note: As this role supports the Australian Public Sector, Australian citizens with the capability to secure and maintain government security clearance are preferred.

Key Responsibilities

Architect and design end-to-end data management and analytics solutions using SAP Business Data Cloud, ensuring scalability, security, and alignment with industry best practices.
Provide strategic advisory to Federal Government clients, developing data strategies and roadmaps that align with public sector objectives and compliance requirements.
Lead and mentor delivery teams, providing technical direction and best practice guidance at both regional and global levels.

Job description:



About the Role

The Manager, Asset Data Reporting and Visualisation is a position that sits within the Asset Information Requirements, Governance and Reporting Team in Asset Intelligence Branch of Assets and Engineering Division. The position leads the on-going management of asset related data reporting and visualisation capabilities that align with business needs, organisational objectives and regulatory requirements.

This position ensures that timely and accurate asset reports and dashboards are available to meet DTP reporting and visualisation decision-making including strategic asset management, asset assurance, monitoring of asset health, lifecycle performance, risks and other asset management activities across the asset lifecycle.

The position plays a critical role in bridging technical data outputs with business needs by collaborating closely with stakeholders across asset management to ensure reporting outputs are aligned with organisational goals and priorities.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position Outcomes / Accountabilities

Asset Data Reporting and Visualisation - The incumbent leads the development, implementation and continuous improvement of asset data reporting and visualisation capabilities that align with organisational objectives and business needs.
Asset Reports and Dashboards Development - The incumbent provides advanced expertise and knowledge in the production, management and improvement of dashboards and reports using tools such as Power BI, Tableau or similar platform to provide clear, targeted and timely reports that contributes to regulatory submissions, audits, and reporting obligations related to asset inventory, condition and performance.
Asset Data Mining and Integration - The incumbent develops methods to obtain/access data from asset custodians and stewards, asset information specialists, and collaborate with data engineers and modellers to ensure data from multiple sources (e.g. Enterprise Asset Management System, GIS, Analytics Platform, SCADA) are harmonised and integrated for reporting.
Asset Trend Analysis - The incumbent applies sound statistical and analytical techniques to build and maintain methodologies to enable trend analysis in asset condition, performance, failure rates to support evidence-based problem solving with respect to asset management lifecycle activities.
Stakeholder Management - The incumbent demonstrates excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to collaborate with a range of internal and external stakeholders to understand business needs and requirements to ensure delivery of value-added reporting solutions.
In line with Section 31A of the Public Administration Act 2004 (Vic) other duties may be assigned consistent with employment classification, skills, and capabilities.

Key Selection Criteria

The DTP is seeking a professional with strong data literacy and reporting expertise to analyse complex datasets, generate meaningful insights, and support effective decision-making. You will apply accomplished critical thinking, stakeholder management, and organisational asset management capabilities to deliver value-add outcomes and drive service improvements. The role also encourages innovation and continuous improvement, contributing ideas and enhancing processes to improve quality and efficiency.

Qualifications and Experience

Mandatory

Tertiary qualifications in data analytics, data science, statistics, asset management and/or engineering related disciplines
Experience in data visualisation development through BI Tools such as Power BI, Tableau
Experience in people management and team leadership
Experience in complex infrastructure, asset and/or engineering data management

Desirable

Experience in one or more programming languages (R, SQL, Python)
Experience in Asset Management, preferably in Transport industry (Roads, Rail, Bus)
Experience in managing geospatial data (Shapefile, GeoJSON, WKT, KML, KMZ) and products (Esri)

Culture Value

We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

What we offer

Meaningful work making Victorian communities more accessible and liveable
Professional growth and development opportunities across the department and the wider Victorian Public Services
A hybrid working model focused on collaboration and teamwork
Optimal work-life balance initiatives including flexible working arrangements
Opportunity to work across multiple urban and suburban hubs
We prioritise the development of a safe and inclusive culture

Pre-employment checks and employment conditions

All new appointments to the department will be subject to a National Criminal Records Check, Misconduct Screening, and a Qualification Check where there is a requirement for a mandatory qualification. Information provided to the Department of Transport and Planning will be treated in the strictest confidence consistent with the requirements of the Privacy and Data Protection Act 2014.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.

Recipients of Victorian Public Service (VPS) voluntary departure packages should note that re-employment restrictions apply.

Non-VPS applicants will be subject to a probation period of six months.

Support Data and Analytics Engineer - 6 month Contract 

Flexible work from home arrangements

Location: North Sydney, 2060




ABOUT EG

Ideas are becoming a reality across the EG Australia national network as we deliver a consistent retail strategy in specialist forecourt retailing to our customers. We continue to build and grow, supported by the knowledge and success of EG Group a creative and innovative global retail operation servicing over 6,500 forecourts in 9 countries across Europe, North America and Australia.




ABOUT THE ROLE

As a Support Data & Analytics Engineer, you’ll provide essential reporting and data support for 500+ stores and key business units, including Finance, Operations, Fuel Pricing, Merchandising, Business Assurance, and People & Culture. You’ll manage and resolve ServiceNow support tickets by identifying root causes, re-running pipelines, validating data quality, and working with upstream system owners to fix data or logic issues.

You’ll also perform analytical investigations to detect issues, anomalies, and trends, collaborating closely with the wider EG Australia Support Team to ensure accurate and reliable information management.




RESPONSIBILITIES IN A SNAPSHOT:

Reporting into the Head of Information Management you will:

Monitor and action support tickets daily in the ServiceNow queue, along with investigating the underlying trends and anomalies

Liaise with internal users and escalate more complex issues to senior engineers or development teams

Processing ensuring all data processing is completed in a timely manner to ensure downstream reporting and analytics are up to date

Design, test and implement effective and scalable data pipelines, leveraging cutting-edge tools such as LucidCharts (to design), SQL (to build) and Azure Data Factory (to schedule)

Design, test and implement effective and scalable data pipelines in Azure Data Factor

Enhance and maintain data storage and processing solutions, across data warehouses and data lakes using Azure.

Automate data analysis and reporting processes, utilising various tools and scripts

Support data governance through implementing best practices around code documentation, naming conventions, data glossaries and data mapping

Partner with stakeholders to translate complex business problems into fit-for-purpose and scalable data pipelines and data models, to enable fast and efficient data-driven decision-making




WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

A Bachelor’s degree in Data Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field

4 years of experience in a data engineering or analytics role, with a strong foundation in working with complex data systems

Strong problem-solving and analytical skills, with a natural curiosity for digging into data and identifying solutions

Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to engage and manage stakeholders effectively

A proactive and collaborative approach, you work well independently and as part of a team

Proficiency in Snowflake and advanced SQL scripting, along with intermediate skills in a programming language such as Python

Hands-on experience with ETL and scheduling tools like Azure Data Factory, Azure Logic Apps, PowerAutomate, or similar platforms

A solid understanding of data modelling principles, practices, and methodologies

Experience creating and maintaining technical documentation, standards, and best-practice guidance

Demonstrated expertise in database design, Master Data Management (MDM), and building high-performance, scalable data pipelines




WHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU?

An opportunity to play an integral role in driving efficiency and profitability for EG Australia.

Competitive salary package and employee discounts.

Mix of office & working from home flexibility with access to employee well-being programs.

Work with cutting edge analytics & AI tools across Azure, Snowflake and DataIKU.

Equal opportunity workplace with a commitment to diversity & inclusion and gender-diverse policies.

 

Be part of the team shaping operations for EG Australia. Apply Now

About us
We create thriving places and connected communities. We bring together transport, planning, land use, precinct and policy functions in a single department to deliver the best outcomes for Victorians.


Together with our portfolio agencies, we are responsible for planning, building, operating and +maintaining Victoria's transport, planning and land services for use by all.


We foster a safe, inclusive and constructive place to work.


Integrated Strategy is a Division within the Office of the Secretary, which provides oversight to policy change and operates as a policy coordination and strategy function within DTP. Integrated Strategy works with external stakeholders and across the Department to co-design policies and strategies to respond to current and future challenges.



Job description:



About the role
This role is in a newly created Strategy Branch in the Integrated Strategy Division of the Department. The purpose of the Branch is to lead longer term strategy work for the Department. Reporting to the Director, the Principal Strategy Advisor will be part of a small team that together with other members of the Integrated Strategy Division will work with leaders from across DTP on high priority strategy topics identified by DTP leadership.


The Principal Strategy Advisor will take a leading role on strategic workstreams through facilitating workshops, designing and executing cross departmental engagement approaches, structuring complex problems and fully owning the delivery of work against them spanning work planning, analysis, synthesising and end product creation.

Key Selection Criteria
The role requires demonstrated leadership in critical thinking, problem solving and project delivery, with the ability to analyse complex issues in a broader organisational context, develop effective solutions and translate strategic direction into successful programs and initiatives. Strong data literacy is essential, including the ability to design data collection and analysis approaches that support informed, predictive decision-making. The position also demands a future-focused mindset, highly effective communication skills and the ability to build a collaborative culture across internal and external stakeholders.

To access the Position Description, please click here.

Position accountabilities
The Department of Transport and Planning is seeking an experienced and influential Principal Strategy Advisor to play a key role in shaping strategic direction across Victoria's transport system. This senior position is responsible for guiding major strategic work, leading complex analysis and ensuring the department's priorities are clearly defined, well-evidenced and aligned with broader organisational goals.


In this role, you will work closely with senior leaders to distil diverse inputs into clear strategic focus areas. You will scope, research and complete complex qualitative and quantitative analysis to inform high-quality written strategy products that support long-term decision-making. Your ability to synthesise information, think critically across multiple time horizons and translate insights into impactful strategy documents will be central to your success.


The role also involves managing projects that underpin the development and implementation of key strategic products. You will coordinate timelines, monitor progress, identify risks and proactively provide solutions, ensuring the Strategy Director is kept informed of critical milestones and challenges. Your leadership will help embed strategic outcomes across the department, ensuring they translate into real and enduring impact.


This is an opportunity to influence State-wide strategic priorities and contribute to shaping the future of transport and planning in Victoria. If you are a strategic thinker with strong analytical capability, excellent stakeholder skills and a commitment to delivering high-quality work, we encourage you to apply.


Qualifications and experience
Mandatory
- Tertiary qualification or extensive experience in an analytical or technical field. (mandatory)
- Experience working with complex and disparate data sets to draw strategic insights (mandatory)
- Exposure to problem structuring and analytical approaches (mandatory)

Desirable
- Knowledge and experience in Transport and/or Planning (desirable)

Culture Value
We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.


As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

Working at the Department of Transport and Planning provides people with the opportunity to contribute to creating thriving places and connected communities for all Victorians.

IXOM plays a vital part in the lives of tens of millions of people every day. We're the experts behind the scenes, ensuring safe and reliable access and helping industries, businesses, and local communities thrive.

We are supported by over 1,300 people globally and our operations span across four continents and nine countries, with headquarters in Melbourne, Australia.





About your role

Reporting to the Head of Business Process Data & Analytics within the Technology & Transformation (T&T) team, the Business Process Analyst will be instrumental in driving meaningful change across IXOM's internal operations. This role is all about uncovering opportunities—identifying and validating process challenges, facilitating stakeholder workshops, and conducting current state assessments to pave the way for smarter, more efficient ways of working.

If you're passionate about process excellence, thrive in collaborative environments, and love turning complexity into clarity, this is your chance to make a lasting impact.

Key Responsibilities

Drive Process Optimisation: Analyse existing processes to identify opportunities for simplification, standardisation, and automation.
Lead Continuous Improvement: Initiate and support process improvement initiatives that enhance efficiency and support strategic goals.
Engage Stakeholders: Facilitate workshops and act as a key liaison between business units, the Technology & Transformation team, and Organisational Change Management.
Document and Communicate Clearly: Develop and maintain comprehensive process documentation, SOPs, and training materials to support change adoption.
Support Project Delivery: Align process work with project timelines and objectives, providing business analysis support and ensuring timely execution.

Who are we looking for?

Bachelor's degree in business Analytics, Business Process Management, Business Management or a related field.
Relevant business process improvement related qualifications including Six Sigma or similar
Proven experience as a Business Analyst or a suitable management role, with a focus on business improvement and optimisation.
Analytical Thinking: Ability to analyse complex processes and identify areas for improvement.
Communication: Strong verbal and written communication skills to effectively interact with stakeholders at all levels.
Attention to Detail: Meticulous attention to detail in process documentation and analysis.
Adaptability: Ability to adapt to changing business needs and priorities.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a keen understanding of business processes.
Familiarity with process mapping.
Familiarity with process mapping standards and tools/technologies (e.g. Signavio) an advantage
Ability to work collaboratively in a team-oriented environment.
Experience participating in projects and supporting deliverables, timelines, and teams.
Understanding of automation and standardisation principles in business processes.

Benefits at IXOM


For a start, you'll work for a large global organisation, where you'll not only earn a competitive salary, but you'll also have access to an Employee Assistance Program, a recognition program, and a range of health and wellness benefits and discounts.

Our wellbeing program is second to none, and we offer a range of education assistance and learning resources, as well as secondment and promotion opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally.

We support what's important to you by promoting workplace giving, diversity and providing volunteering leave, and, of course, we offer flexible working wherever possible.

To Apply

If this sounds like you, we'd love to hear from you!

Our Process

At IXOM we are committed to employing individuals who align with our values and meet the requirements of the role. As part of the recruitment process, there are a number of checks which may be conducted to demonstrate applicants' suitability for a role including police / criminal background checks, medical, drug and alcohol testing, and reference checks.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition team.

Careers with Impact

More than one million Australians trust HESTA with their money. HESTA is a top-performing industry super fund working for real-world impact. We use our expertise and influence to deliver strong long-term returns while accelerating our contribution to a more sustainable world.

HESTA is also an inspiring and rewarding place to work. That's because what we do makes a difference to the lives of our members. The people who work at HESTA are not only exceptional at what they do, they're focused on living and creating a strong organisational culture. Bring your authentic and passionate self to this exceptional role #careerswithimpact

Please note this role could be based in Sydney or Melbourne.


As the Senior Investment Analyst - Fixed Income, you will support the Defensive Assets team in the implementation and oversight of HESTA's internal Fixed Income, Cash and Enhanced Cash portfolio management activities.

Reporting to the Portfolio Manager - Fixed Income, you will be involved in portfolio management support, including portfolio construction, risk management, and trade idea generation based on quantitative analysis. Leading quantitative research initiatives, you will develop and refine investment processes while identifying new portfolio construction opportunities through data-driven analysis.

Your role will encompass risk management and compliance responsibilities, ensuring adherence to investment mandates and contributing to our risk management framework. You will design and implement quantitative models for interest rate and credit analysis, while creating and maintaining portfolio optimization tools.

About You

Essential for this role is experience in fixed income portfolio management combined with skills and experience in Debt Capital Markets and in the practical application of quantitative methodologies and techniques to Fixed Income Portfolio Management and Trade Execution.

The ideal candidate will possess qualifications in Finance, Actuarial Studies, Econometrics or related fields, along with intermediate to advanced skills in Python and/or R. Required experience includes financial modelling, yield curve analysis, portfolio construction, derivatives trading, relative value analysis and risk management in a Portfolio Management or Dealing Room environment. You will have well developed sector knowledge of defensive asset classes (credit, debt, cash) and FX and experience in portfolio construction and risk management.

Process Analyst 
 
Project Overview:
Our client in the leisure space is transitioning from its legacy on-premise Opera PMS (v5.6) to Oracle's Opera Cloud platform across 10 Club and Resort properties, including Opera Sales & Catering (S&C) for Conference & Events. This migration will modernize operations, reduce on-premise infrastructure, and enable industry-standard features.

Role Details

Location: Melbourne, Victoria
Contract: 6-Month Contingent
Work Model: Hybrid (3 days in-office)
Key Responsibilities

Analyse and document current-state business processes and define future-state workflows aligned with Opera Cloud capabilities.
Collaborate with delivery teams to ensure process changes are implemented effectively during system configuration and migration.
Conduct impact assessments for process changes across hospitality operations and Conference & Events.
Support testing activities by validating process alignment during SIT and UAT phases.
Facilitate workshops with stakeholders to confirm process requirements and resolve gaps.
Develop process documentation, SOPs, and training materials to support operational readiness.
Identify risks and dependencies related to process changes and escalate as needed.
Skills & Experience

Strong background in business process analysis and modelling (BPMN or similar).
Experience in hospitality or leisure industry systems, ideally PMS platforms.
Ability to manage stakeholder engagement and drive consensus on process changes.
Familiarity with cloud migration projects and integration considerations.
Proficiency with Jira, Confluence, and process modelling tools (Visio, draw.io).
Agile delivery experience and ability to work in fast-paced environments.

LTI Mindtree is seeking an experienced Azure Analytics Data Architect to lead the design and delivery of enterprise-grade Azure data platforms for public sector and large enterprise clients. This role requires strong expertise across Azure analytics services, data engineering best practices, and cloud architectural governance. The ideal candidate will bring deep technical capability, architectural leadership, and the ability to design secure, scalable, and future-ready data ecosystems. Active NV1/NV2 security clearance is mandatory.

Key Responsibilities

Architect and implement end-to-end Azure data solutions spanning ingestion, storage, processing, analytics, and governance.
Define and maintain enterprise-wide Azure data architecture standards that align with security, compliance, and operational frameworks.
Utilize key Azure services such as Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, Synapse Analytics, Data Lake Storage, Data Factory, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL to deliver high-performing solutions.
Build, optimize, and automate scalable ETL/ELT pipelines using ADF, Synapse, metadata-driven frameworks, and CI/CD practices.
Provide architectural leadership across data modeling, integration workflows, analytics pipelines, and cross-system interoperability.
Implement strong data governance, data quality, identity controls, and privacy protection across Azure environments.
Collaborate with data scientists, analysts, and application teams to deliver structured, governed, and accessible datasets.
Create and maintain architecture documentation, solution blueprints, and implementation roadmaps.
Ensure architecture alignment with Microsoft Cloud Adoption Framework (CAF), Well-Architected Framework (WAF), and organizational technology standards.
Drive continuous improvement across performance, reliability, cost optimization, operational excellence, and security posture.
Qualifications

Active NV1/NV2 Security Clearance (mandatory, role cannot be performed without it)
10+ years of experience in Data Architecture, Data Engineering, Cloud Analytics, or enterprise data platform delivery
Deep hands-on expertise with Azure analytics services including Data Factory, Synapse, Databricks, Data Lake, Fabric, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL
Strong knowledge of data modeling, warehousing concepts, ETL/ELT best practices, and distributed data processing
Experience working with both relational and NoSQL data systems, including PostgreSQL and Cosmos DB
Proven capability in designing scalable, secure, and governed cloud architectures at enterprise scale
Experience with CI/CD, infrastructure-as-code, metadata-driven frameworks, and modern DevOps practices
Exceptional communication, documentation, and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to convey complex architecture concepts to both technical and business audiences

At LTI Mindtree Australia, you’ll have the opportunity to work on nation-critical transformation programs while being part of a global organization known for innovation, excellence, and a strong Azure data practice. You will join a collaborative team that values technical leadership, continuous learning, and impactful delivery. This is your chance to shape the data landscape for some of the region’s most strategic clients, all while growing your career in a supportive and future-focused environment.

Category: Policy, Planning & Regulation, Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Your new opportunity:
As a Principal Treasury Analyst, you will lead the monitoring and analysis of financial and non-financial performance across Queensland Government agencies, providing strategic advice to support the development and implementation of sound public policy.

This is an exciting opportunity to work with internal and external clients and stakeholders to address complex financial and policy matters, identify risks, and develop strategic solutions that align with the Government's economic priorities. You will play a critical role in delivering high-quality advice, reports and recommendations to senior executives, ministerial offices and interdepartmental committees, ensuring that Queensland Treasury continues to drive the state's economic growth and sustainability.

In this role, you will:
• Provide strategic advice and support to clients and senior executives on complex budget, financial management, and policy issues.
• Lead the development and implementation of processes to monitor and analyse agencies' budget and financial information.
• Offer expert advice on risk identification, management, and evaluation of best practice financial strategies and policies.
• Manage relationships with clients and stakeholders to resolve complex issues and negotiate positive outcomes.
• Represent Treasury on internal and external committees and interdepartmental working groups.
• Prepare complex reports, submissions, briefing notes, and correspondence within tight timeframes.
• Support organisational strategy, direction, and initiatives.

What experience you will bring:
To excel in this role, you will demonstrate:
• The ability to lead teams and deliver outcomes in a complex and time-sensitive environment.
• Experience in analysing financial and non-financial performance data and/or developing government policy.
• Expertise in providing strategic, practical, and solutions-focused analysis and advice.
• Influential communication skills tailored to diverse audiences.
• Strong interpersonal and relationship management skills to foster collaboration and information sharing.
• Effective judgement and understanding of different perspectives to develop solutions and work collaboratively.

Whilst there are no mandatory qualifications needed for this role, relevant qualifications will be highly regarded.

How to apply:
To submit your application, click on the Apply link to provide:
• Your resume detailing relevant experience.
• A cover letter of no more than two pages outlining why you are interested in this position and how your knowledge, skills and experience makes you a strong candidate for the role.
